   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Retain Teachers in Uganda School for 650 Students</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Retaining good teachers is the key to a quality education.  Bishop Comboni College Kambuga, in SW Uganda, is a highly rated secondary school with 620 boarding students.  Teacher effectiveness is the key to student performance.  The major incentive for recruiting and retaining quality teachers is to provide clean and safe housing. An area on the campus is being developed for a Faculty Housing Community.  The school&apos;s outstanding academic performance will continue with continuity in teachers.</narrative>
  </description>
